<i>but it is unstoppable.</i>

134
00:09:25.631 --> 00:09:30.703  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>In order to avoid any further victims,</i>
<i>we are hoping for a swift response.</i>

135
00:09:31.938 --> 00:09:33.739  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>We're expecting a good one.</i>

136
00:09:37.643 --> 00:09:40.746  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I wonder how the government's
going to react to that.

137
00:09:41.647 --> 00:09:43.049  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's nothing to wonder about.

138
00:09:43.716 --> 00:09:45.952  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They only ever have one answer.

139
00:09:47.253 --> 00:09:50.623  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man 1] Prime Minister! How do you intend
to respond to Sato's demands?

140
00:09:50.690 --> 00:09:53.359  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As there have been absolutely
no experiments on Ajin,

141
00:09:53.960 --> 00:09:55.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can only face this situation
with resolve.

142
00:09:56.028 --> 00:09:58.364  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man 2] But aren't there indications

143
00:09:58.631 --> 00:10:01.901  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that Tanaka was experimented on
while under government protection?

144
00:10:01.968 --> 00:10:03.336  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I will tell you this.</i>

145
00:10:03.970 --> 00:10:06.872  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>The government will not yield</i>
<i>to terrorists.</i>

146
00:10:07.139 --> 00:10:10.910  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>We will stand firm,</i>
<i>and resolve this situation quickly.</i>

147
00:10:14.113 --> 00:10:15.982  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You really shouldn't get your hopes up.

148
00:10:16.616 --> 00:10:18.050  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They make me sick.

149
00:10:18.117 --> 00:10:19.385  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's all right.

150
00:10:20.252 --> 00:10:24.290  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If that's how they want to be,
we just need to act decisively is all.

151
00:10:25.825 --> 00:10:27.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Sato, got a sec?

152
00:10:28.761 --> 00:10:29.929  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, of course.

153
00:10:31.764 --> 00:10:33.199  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What the heck is he doing?

154
00:10:33.866 --> 00:10:35.234  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's been working on it for ages.

155
00:10:35.301 --> 00:10:36.168  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mm?

156
00:10:36.235 --> 00:10:39.205  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[laughs] That's our secret weapon.

157
00:10:40.339 --> 00:10:41.374  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

158
00:10:49.782 --> 00:10:51.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Tosaki] They're shaping up nicely.

159
00:10:51.784 --> 00:10:54.286  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man] That's because we've been
really pushing them physically.

160
00:10:54.353 --> 00:10:55.721  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[blows whistle]

161
00:10:56.188 --> 00:10:57.289  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[groaning]

162
00:11:05.998 --> 00:11:08.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[Tosaki] What about that one matter?
-Tomorrow.

163
00:11:08.834 --> 00:11:12.004  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Once preparations are complete,
move on to the next phase

164
00:11:12.405 --> 00:11:13.305  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, sir.

165
00:11:13.806 --> 00:11:14.740  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[woman] Mr. Tosaki.

166
00:11:15.207 --> 00:11:17.243  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We got a message from Sokabe.

167
00:11:17.777 --> 00:11:19.979  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He said there's a special meeting
this afternoon.

168
00:11:20.046 --> 00:11:20.946  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Special meeting?

169
00:11:21.914 --> 00:11:25.084  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-About the Forge Security issue?
-No, it's...

170
00:11:25.151 --> 00:11:28.354  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Some people are coming
from the U.S. Department of Defense.

171
00:11:39.331 --> 00:11:42.368  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This doesn't look like
a Control Commission meeting to me.

172
00:11:43.002 --> 00:11:44.837  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's the Department of Defense, right?

173
00:11:45.237 --> 00:11:48.307  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They might have some advice
for anti-Ajin measures.

174
00:11:49.041 --> 00:11:49.942  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Advice?

175
00:11:51.110 --> 00:11:53.045  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Like it's their place to interfere.

176
00:11:54.246 --> 00:11:56.182  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sokabe hasn't told you anything, right?

177
00:11:56.816 --> 00:12:00.186  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Apparently, Sokabe doesn't know
any of the details either.

178
00:12:01.487 --> 00:12:03.222  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Right this way, please.

179
00:12:06.425 --> 00:12:07.860  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you for your patience.

180
00:12:08.360 --> 00:12:14.166  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This is Douglas Almeida and Carly Myers
of the U.S. Department of Defense.

181
00:12:15.334 --> 00:12:16.302  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Please, go ahead.

182
00:12:17.069 --> 00:12:20.039  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
First of all, we appreciate
you making time for us.

183
00:12:20.906 --> 00:12:24.176  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We've been sent here
to launch a full investigation

184
00:12:24.243 --> 00:12:27.046  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
on the deaths of Dr. Ogura
and his bodyguard.

185
00:12:27.413 --> 00:12:30.516  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Both of whom were killed
in Sato's recent attack.

186
00:12:32.418 --> 00:12:36.055  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Therefore, we've asked everyone who was
at the research facility on that day

187
00:12:36.122 --> 00:12:37.189  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to join us here today.

188
00:12:37.823 --> 00:12:42.828  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Actually, our own investigations prove
they were definitely killed by Sato.

189
00:12:43.762 --> 00:12:45.764  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is further investigation necessary?

190
00:12:45.831 --> 00:12:49.235  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yes, and this matter involves
a great deal of classified information.

191
00:12:49.802 --> 00:12:51.871  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We'd much rather not
have you sniffing around.

192
00:12:51.937 --> 00:12:55.541  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Almeida] Our plans have already been
cleared with the Japanese government.

193
00:12:57.076 --> 00:12:58.811  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're too busy for this now.

194
00:12:59.278 --> 00:13:01.046  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You realize it's very rare

195
00:13:01.380 --> 00:13:06.185  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
for U.S. personnel to be injured or killed
in a foreign research facility.

196
00:13:07.119 --> 00:13:10.189  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So, the Department of Defense must have
a detailed understanding

197
00:13:10.256 --> 00:13:12.024  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
of the circumstances of their deaths.

198
00:13:12.558 --> 00:13:13.893  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
During the investigation,

199
00:13:13.959 --> 00:13:17.997  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we'll be asking each one of you
exactly what happened on that day.

200
00:13:18.330 --> 00:13:20.032  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We appreciate your help.

201
00:13:20.099 --> 00:13:22.268  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
More things we have to worry about.

202
00:13:22.334 --> 00:13:24.236  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[men whispering]
Why are we being investigated?

203
00:13:24.303 --> 00:13:26.205  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are we getting interviewed individually?

204
00:13:26.472 --> 00:13:28.541  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Those black suits were from the Pentagon?

205
00:13:32.244 --> 00:13:35.214  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Mr. Tosaki, what should we--?
-We're fine.

206
00:13:35.281 --> 00:13:39.051  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I erased the security video
of me shooting the bodyguard,

207
00:13:39.118 --> 00:13:40.486  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and doctored the dental records

208
00:13:40.553 --> 00:13:43.255  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
of the researcher
whose body I used in place of Ogura's.

209
00:13:44.990 --> 00:13:48.527  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But... we're going to need to come up
with a solid cover story.

210
00:13:49.828 --> 00:13:51.897  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Put together all the records for that day.

211
00:13:52.565 --> 00:13:53.465  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, sir.

212
00:14:03.209 --> 00:14:06.111  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn it. Why now, of all times?

213
00:14:15.020 --> 00:14:20.059  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We can't see IBMs with our eyes,
but there are ways to detect them.

214
00:14:23.495 --> 00:14:24.530  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Go ahead, walk.

215
00:14:25.531 --> 00:14:27.132  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Shut up.

216
00:14:30.936 --> 00:14:32.137  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nakano.

217
00:14:32.204 --> 00:14:33.272  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
On it!

218
00:14:39.511 --> 00:14:41.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If you run into one directly...

219
00:14:42.147 --> 00:14:43.649  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
there are ways to take them down.

220
00:14:45.150 --> 00:14:47.186  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know, just like a woman.

221
00:14:47.987 --> 00:14:51.423  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But of course, in the field,
it won't be this easy.

222
00:14:53.092 --> 00:14:56.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The most reliable approach
is to knock out the Ajin that summoned it.

223
00:14:59.231 --> 00:15:03.569  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
With a normal IBM,
that will neutralize them.

224
00:15:10.576 --> 00:15:12.978  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You've got him pretty well housebroken.

225
00:15:13.245 --> 00:15:14.313  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm.

226
00:15:24.356 --> 00:15:26.492  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[thud then Kotobuki gasps]

227
00:15:27.960 --> 00:15:31.330  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Wake up, Kotobuki.
This is the last time I'm gonna ask you.

228
00:15:32.998 --> 00:15:34.967  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You don't know when to give up.

229
00:15:35.434 --> 00:15:37.703  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I bet you drive your girlfriend crazy.

230
00:15:39.104 --> 00:15:40.439  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

231
00:15:49.081 --> 00:15:50.482  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kotobuki screams]

232
00:15:54.453 --> 00:15:57.289  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My girl's birthday is tomorrow.

233
00:15:59.191 --> 00:16:02.728  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You do this and you're not going
to be getting out of here for a while.

234
00:16:03.429 --> 00:16:04.596  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whatever.

235
00:16:04.663 --> 00:16:07.199  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's no point if I can't get out today.

236
00:16:17.176 --> 00:16:18.110  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kaito] <i>That's right.</i>

237
00:16:19.345 --> 00:16:23.682  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Just stay right there,</i>
<i>pretend you don't see anything.</i>

238
00:16:27.019 --> 00:16:28.220  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>It's just your imagination.</i>

239
00:16:30.622 --> 00:16:34.259  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Two days from now</i>
<i>I will start a protest movement!</i>

240
00:16:34.426 --> 00:16:37.663  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>It'll take place in front of</i>
<i>the Ministry of Health, Labor and Welfare!</i>

241
00:16:38.564 --> 00:16:41.734  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kotobuki] <i>It was my hesitation.</i>

242
00:16:43.102 --> 00:16:44.303  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thanks for coming.

243
00:16:45.337 --> 00:16:48.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now I'll tell you
the real gathering place.

244
00:16:48.741 --> 00:16:52.444  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I don't know about you, but I'm going.
-Me, too.

245
00:16:54.613 --> 00:16:56.615  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kotobuki] <i>What should I do?</i>

246
00:16:58.450 --> 00:17:02.054  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So, are you going to head
to the gathering place?

247
00:17:02.121 --> 00:17:03.155  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

248
00:17:03.655 --> 00:17:05.524  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, seems like a pain.

249
00:17:06.792 --> 00:17:08.460  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kotobuki] <i>Yeah, he's probably right.</i>

250
00:17:13.265 --> 00:17:16.068  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Look, if you don't wanna die,
then just tell me.

251
00:17:34.586 --> 00:17:36.088  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You bastard.

252
00:17:42.261 --> 00:17:44.663  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kotobuki] <i>What's wrong with this idiot?</i>

253
00:18:00.512 --> 00:18:02.214  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>No, he's not an idiot.</i>

254
00:18:06.618 --> 00:18:07.853  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>He's a complete moron.</i>

255
00:18:12.524 --> 00:18:13.592  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasping]

256
00:18:19.765 --> 00:18:22.868  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Didn't I tell you that I'd kill you?

257
00:18:51.463 --> 00:18:53.198  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[wheezing]

258
00:19:08.313 --> 00:19:09.815  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Basic training is done.

259
00:19:11.617 --> 00:19:13.552  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Starting today, it's field training.

260
00:19:18.257 --> 00:19:19.558  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] Sorry for taking so long.

261
00:19:19.625 --> 00:19:22.628  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, no, this is great.

262
00:19:23.762 --> 00:19:26.765  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Once this is done,
we're gonna have a hell of a lot of fun.

263
00:19:27.566 --> 00:19:31.803  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yeah, well, no one else
could come up with this.

264
00:19:33.238 --> 00:19:36.542  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But making it is going to take
a whole lot of explosives.

265
00:19:37.442 --> 00:19:38.710  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That won't be a problem.

266
00:19:39.478 --> 00:19:43.182  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We have some leftovers
from what Nekozawa provided us last time.

267
00:19:44.650 --> 00:19:45.784  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now, then...

268
00:19:48.520 --> 00:19:50.589  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
how about we breeze through
the second half...

269
00:19:51.223 --> 00:19:54.359  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
so we can use our secret weapon?

270
00:20:03.435 --> 00:20:04.736  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kotobuki grunts]

271
00:20:05.604 --> 00:20:06.471  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Smoke?

272
00:20:09.908 --> 00:20:11.843  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I hear they're all being put in solitary.

273
00:20:12.578 --> 00:20:14.313  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And they won't be out for a while.

274
00:20:17.282 --> 00:20:20.219  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I have a secret supplier.
Don't look into it.

275
00:20:36.768 --> 00:20:39.838  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey... what kind of guy is Kei Nagai?

276
00:20:43.809 --> 00:20:44.676  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kei is...

277
00:20:46.411 --> 00:20:47.412  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
a good friend.

278
00:20:48.647 --> 00:20:49.514  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My first one.

279
00:20:49.848 --> 00:20:51.450  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But he left you behind, right?

280
00:20:52.351 --> 00:20:53.485  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Aren't you pissed?

281
00:20:54.553 --> 00:20:56.622  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If he doesn't need my help, I'll back off.

282
00:20:58.624 --> 00:21:00.525  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But if anything happens, I'm there.

283
00:21:01.693 --> 00:21:03.262  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No matter what it takes.

284
00:21:05.998 --> 00:21:06.999  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Know what?

285
00:21:07.799 --> 00:21:09.001  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You really are annoying.

286
00:21:10.802 --> 00:21:11.670  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah...

287
00:21:12.738 --> 00:21:13.672  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know.

288
00:21:20.445 --> 00:21:22.347  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hypothetically, Kaito...

289
00:21:23.749 --> 00:21:26.618  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
let's say something happens
to Kei Nagai...

290
00:21:27.619 --> 00:21:30.322  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and you really need
to get out of this dump.

291
00:21:31.623 --> 00:21:32.557  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You come talk to me.

292
00:21:36.995 --> 00:21:38.497  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll only do it once...

293
00:21:39.331 --> 00:21:41.033  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but I'll get you over this wall.

294
00:21:49.875 --> 00:21:51.977  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
TO BE CONTINUED

295
00:21:53.312 --> 00:21:56.348  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[chorus singing]
<i>I'm tired of this one already, so</i>

296
00:21:56.415 --> 00:21:59.618  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I'll trade it</i>

297
00:21:59.685 --> 00:22:04.823  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>For your ordinary one</i>

298
00:22:05.957 --> 00:22:11.997  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>A shiny holy card</i>

299
00:22:12.464 --> 00:22:17.436  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>For a grainy paper card</i>

300
00:22:18.637 --> 00:22:22.841  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>You can see them all</i>

301
00:22:25.077 --> 00:22:29.047  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>When you come to my house</i>

302
00:22:29.681 --> 00:22:35.721  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>So</i>
<i>Two of us in the corner of the schoolyard</i>

303
00:22:35.787 --> 00:22:37.889  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>While the wind blows</i>

304
00:22:37.956 --> 00:22:43.462  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I might be able to say it now</i>

305
00:22:44.463 --> 00:22:50.669  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Words I've never said to anyone</i>

306
00:22:50.736 --> 00:22:56.975  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>"Won't you come and play, I'll be nice"</i>

307
00:22:57.042 --> 00:23:02.681  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>"I'll give you anything, see"</i>

308
00:23:03.615 --> 00:23:06.384  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>"Be my friend</i>

309
00:23:06.451 --> 00:23:13.091  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Always"</i>

